   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Resiliency and Sustainable Agribusiness in Typhoon-Damaged Areas of Central Philippines</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heifer launched the Building Resiliency and Sustainable Agribusiness in Typhoon-Damaged Areas of Central Philippines Project, commonly known as the BRESA-Haiyan Rehabilitation Project, in June 2014 to help families rebuild and move them from vulnerability to resiliency. The project aims to assist a total of 5,000 families - 1,000 original families and another 4,000 families through the practice of Passing on the Gift&#xAE; (POG) - by developing small sustainable agribusinesses in the goat and swine value chains.</narrative>
  </description>
